-- German KfW Lends Serbia $130 Million for Farmers, Municipalities
-- B y   G o r d a n a   F i l i p o v i c
-- 2012-12-12T14:29:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-12/german-kfw-lends-serbia-130-million-for-farmers-municipalities.html
German development bank
Kreditanstalt Fuer Wiederaufbau, or KfW, lent Serbia 100 million
euros ($130.4 million) to finance its agriculture,  energy
efficiency , municipal infrastructure and renewable energy.  The funds will be channeled through three Serbian banks
with clients benefiting from seven-year loans, including a two-
year grace period, central bank governor Jorgovanka Tabakovic
told reporters in Belgrade today, adding that Narodna Banka
Srbije will control the cost of borrowing of ultimate clients.  Komercijalna Banka AD (KMBN)  will distribute 30 million euros
worth of loans to farmers and food makers and 25 million euros
to municipalities to repair local water-supply and sewerage
systems and upgrade roads, power grids or heating at schools and
hospitals. ProCredit Bank AD will on-lend 40 million euros to
food makers and farmers for new machinery, cattle, and
investment in organic foods, while  Cacanska Banka AD (CCNB)  will have 5
million euros for energy efficiency and renewable energy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gordana Filipovic in Belgrade at 
